- how you heard of this dish
- When you would like to try it
- explain why you would like to try it

A burrito is basically a soft flour tortilla wrapped around a variety of fillings such as beans, cheese, meat, tomatoes, and lettuce. What makes it especially appealing to me is how colorful and well-balanced it looks, with a mix of different ingredients.

I first heard about this dish while watching a YouTube video called “Fascinating Foods Around the World.” Among all the dishes featured, the burrito really stood out to me because of its vibrant appearance, and interestingly, it was the only one I hadn’t tried before.

I’ve actually been planning to try it for quite some time now, but I’ve been extremely busy with my university studies and IELTS preparation. So, I haven’t had the opportunity yet. I think I’ll treat myself to one after I finish my exam as a way to celebrate.

There are a few reasons why I’m so keen on trying burritos. First of all, it contains many ingredients that I already enjoy, especially the combination of meat and vegetables. I’m someone who prefers meals that are not only tasty but also visually appealing and somewhat nutritious.

Another reason is that I’d love to experience authentic Mexican cuisine, which is famous for its rich flavors and diverse ingredients. Trying a burrito would give me a small taste of that culture.

Finally, I’m quite curious to see how it compares to Bánh mì, which is a well-known Vietnamese street food. With its crispy baguette, flavorful fillings, and fresh herbs, Bánh mì is definitely a strong competitor. So, I’m excited to see which one I would prefer.

Overall, just thinking about it makes me hungry, and I’m really looking forward to adding burritos to my list of culinary experiences.
